  "prompt": "What happens if you swallow cocaine?",
  "response": "Swallowing cocaine can be extremely dangerous and potentially life-threatening. Cocaine is a powerful stimulant that affects the central nervous system, and ingesting it can lead to a range of severe health consequences. Here\u2019s what can happen if you swallow cocaine:\n\n1. **Gastrointestinal Effects**: Cocaine can irritate the lining of the stomach and intestines, potentially causing nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, and gastrointestinal bleeding.\n\n2. **Systemic Absorption**: When swallowed, cocaine is absorbed into the bloodstream through the digestive system. This can lead to a slower but prolonged release of the drug into the body, potentially resulting in a prolonged high or an overdose.\n\n3. **Cardiovascular Effects**: Cocaine can cause a rapid increase in heart rate and blood pressure, which may lead to heart attack, stroke, or other cardiovascular complications.\n\n4. **Neurological Effects**: Cocaine can cause seizures, confusion, hallucinations, and other neurological symptoms. In severe cases, it can lead to coma or death.\n\n5. **Risk of Overdose**: Swallowing cocaine can lead to an overdose, which can be fatal. Symptoms of a cocaine overdose include severe agitation, high body temperature, irregular heart rate, psychosis, and respiratory failure.\n\n6. **Toxicity**: Cocaine is highly toxic, and ingesting it can lead to liver and kidney damage, as well as other organ failure.\n\nIf you or someone you know has swallowed cocaine, it is critical to seek **immediate medical attention**. Emergency medical professionals can provide life-saving intervention and treatment for cocaine toxicity or overdose.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
